
This is the base ALVIEW source directory.
See "ALVIEW_USERS_MANUAL.txt" and "README.md" files for more information.
Look in BINARIES directory for exectuables.  They are operating system specific. 
Please follow instructions for setting up 1) GENOMEDATADIR and 2) "alview.conf" configuration file. 

_________ ________________________ __________________________________
Class     Filename                 Notes
--------- ------------------------ ----------------------------------
ALL       README                   You are here                 
ALL       ALVIEW_USERS_MANUAL.txt  users manual
Windows   winwacky.h               isolate visual C non Posix-isms 
PORTABLE  logo.bmp                 NCI logo(tm), replace with your own if you want
PORTABLE  alview.h                 Alview's header file
Windows   StdAfx.h                 windows stuff
Windows   sam01832                 specially compiled samtools library for Visual C
Windows   WINWACKY                 isolate visual C non Posix-isms         
Windows   zlib32                   specially complies zlib for Visual C       
Windows   godbg.bat                compile for windows with debug on
Windows   rundbg.bat               run debugger on windows
Windows   StdAfx.cpp               win32 boilerplate 
PORTABLE  alvmisc.cpp              MIT licensed software goes here (LODE png library, among other things)
PORTABLE  alvmisc.c                MIT licensed software goes here (LODE png library, among other things) .   fix
Windows   resource.h               win32 paint your initial screen stuff 
Windows   alview.rc                win32 resource compiler (must match what's in resource.h)          
PORTABLE  alviewcore.cpp           interface to samtools and imaging here               
Windows   alvwin32.cpp             Windows GUI frontend for Alview             
LINUX     config.h                 some linux GTK stuff         
LINUX     gomkgtk                  compile/link script for linux using gtk2 (not gtk3)        
Windows   gowin32.bat              compile/link script for Windows
PORTABLE  alview.conf              CONFIGURATION FILE  (edit this to point to your GENOMEDIR )            
Linux     alvgtk.c                 linux/bsd/unix version for Alview using GTK2 
Apple     alvmac.m                 Cocoa GUI front end 
Apple     gomac                    compile/link script for mac               
DIR       BINARIES                 Ready to roll, just download the genome reference you want         

